name: Propranolol hydrochloride
warningsAndPrecautions:
Propranolol Hydrochloride Tablets, USP 80 mg – Yellow, round biconvex scored tablets with “I” “161” on one side and other side plain. 
                  NDC: 71335-2594-5: 10 Tablets in a BOTTLE
                  NDC: 71335-2594-1: 30 Tablets in a BOTTLE
                  NDC: 71335-2594-2: 100 Tablets in a BOTTLE
                  NDC: 71335-2594-3: 90 Tablets in a BOTTLE
                  NDC: 71335-2594-4: 60 Tablets in a BOTTLE
                  
                  Repackaged/Relabeled by:Bryant Ranch Prepack, Inc.Burbank, CA 91504
adverseReactions: Propranolol is contraindicated in 1) cardiogenic shock; 2) sinus bradycardia and greater than first degree block; 3) bronchial asthma; and 4) in patients with known hypersensitivity to propranolol hydrochloride.
